The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for bioresorbable scaffold visualization using intravascular optical coherence tomography (IVOCT) images. This involves training a convolutional neural network (CNN) for stent classification and using weakly supervised localization with saliency maps for stent strut information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging (cs.MS) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with IVOCT images and stent visualization.
